summary: if Crowley can like Queen then Aziraphale can definitely love ABBA
body:
if Crowley can like Queen then Aziraphale can definitely love ABBA

though on the downlow. It’s his guilty pleasure outside of musicals and classic. He was first introduced to them when Mamma Mia came out as a movie musical and then he fell into a downward spiral from there.

Waterloo is his favorite, followed very closely by Dancing Queen.

(Crowley later catches wind of him singing along in the shower when he thinks he’s alone. He makes a note to never actually tell Aziraphale that he knows, but to tease him just enough to make the Angel think he just might.)

summary: Good Omens..... THEY ARE IN LOVE!
body:
Good Omens….. THEY ARE IN LOVE!

When I was watching the third episode of Good Omens, just like a lot of people I realised Everyone’s Favourite angel fell in love during the church scene!

While Crowley fell in love during the 80s scene!

Someone has pointed out that when they said;

“To The World”

What they were actually saying was,

“I love you”

And am I the only one who thinks the song at the end of the last episode would have been they’re wedding song?!

You can just imagine the two of them slowly dancing cheek to cheek to the song!
